<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF306A8FFF7F9B651634B802" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF306A8FFF7F9B651C8AB6B1" blockId="203.[130,1338,3388,3466]" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF306A8FFF7F9B651F1CB66F" bold="true" box="[131,284,3388,3421]" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FFED69B651CD0B66F" authority="Dobson, 1873" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1873" box="[298,720,3388,3421]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipes">Vespertilio longipes Dobson, 1873</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="74FC3CA3FF306A8FFD1C9B651C8AB6B1" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3783319316" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">
“caves of Bhima Devi, in Kashmir [
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FFB449B651B08B66F" box="[1208,1288,3388,3421]" name="India" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">India</collectingCountry>
], at an elevation of 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF306A8FFEA49B3F1FD5B6B1" box="[344,469,3430,3459]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8288" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" unit="ft" value="6000.0">6000 feet</quantity>
[= 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF306A8FFDFB9B3F1C70B6B1" box="[519,624,3430,3459]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.829" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" unit="m" value="1829.0">1829 m</quantity>
].”
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF306A8FF812974C1634B802" blockId="203.[2027,2622,277,698]" lastBlockId="203.[1411,2622,705,2397]" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF77C974C176DBA00" authority="Kaup, 1829" baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[2176,2413,277,306]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" species="siligorensis">Myotis; siligorensis</taxonomicName>
species group. See 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF7D6976116B3BA6B" authorityName="Topal" authorityYear="1998" box="[2090,2227,312,345]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="csorbai">M. csorbai</taxonomicName>
. G. E. Dobson in 1872 first described this species using the preoccupied name 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF74097DE1733BA9A" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[2236,2355,391,424]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropus">macropus</taxonomicName>
and provided the complete type locality given here; when he realized his error, he renamed the species 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF79997A416C9B92C" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1873" box="[2149,2249,509,542]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipes">longipes</taxonomicName>
in 1873 and only mentioned “Kashmir” as the collection area. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF812941216B3B95E" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[2030,2227,587,620]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipes">Myotis longipes</taxonomicName>
appears to be restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF81794221697B9A6" box="[2027,2199,635,660]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF75094221722B9A6" box="[2220,2338,635,660]" name="Pakistan" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, and north-western 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF81194C01638B988" box="[2029,2104,665,698]" name="India" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">India</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF7B594C016CDB988" authorityName="Topal" authorityYear="1998" box="[2121,2253,665,698]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="csorbai">M. csorbai</taxonomicName>
might be more widely distributed in 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF306A8FF9CC949818C7B9D0" box="[1584,1735,705,738]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF894949819BEB9D0" box="[1896,1982,705,738]" name="China" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">China</collectingCountry>
, and central 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF778949816C4B9D0" box="[2180,2244,705,738]" name="Laos" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Laos</collectingCountry>
but is restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF6169498143DB9D0" box="[2538,2621,705,738]" name="Nepal" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Nepal</collectingCountry>
until other specimens can be assessed to confirm their identity as being 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FF65D94B11437B83B" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[2465,2615,744,777]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipes">M. longipes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF306A8FFA749556180DB802" authorityName="Topal" authorityYear="1998" box="[1416,1549,783,816]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="csorbai">M. csorbai</taxonomicName>
, or an entirely new species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF306A8FFA7B956E1850B84D" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF306A8FFA7B956E1850B84D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398914" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398914/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="203" pageNumber="965" targetBox="[1413,2005,285,699]" targetPageId="203">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF306A8FFA7B956E1850B84D" blockId="203.[1411,2622,705,2397]" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF306A8FFA7B956E1837B86A" bold="true" box="[1415,1591,823,856]" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only definitely from NE 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF867956E1647B86A" box="[1947,2119,823,856]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, N 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF78B956E16EDB86A" box="[2167,2285,823,856]" name="Pakistan" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, and NW 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF306A8FF684956E17C2B86A" box="[2424,2498,823,856]" name="India" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF306A8FF62B956E1843B84D" country="India" name="Jammu and Kashmir" pageId="203" pageNumber="965">Jammu and Kashmir</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
